page.title: 09HOUSING IN MEOPHAM
page.content: Most of the houses lie in the west of the block,along and to both sides of the main road. This area is called Meopham. There is a mixture of old houses, many built about lOO years ago, and new houses built in cul_de_sacs and estates. The older terraced houses are near the station, but there are other terraces of between ten and twelve cottages, which we think were occupied by farm workers. They are now owner_occupied. Some of the old larger houses are occupied by many families. Throughout the block there are many scattered houses along the road sides, some are large detatched dwellings with big gardens, but some are small bungalows.
